data.description: Meticulously maintained cape nestled on a manicured wooded lot. Pushed back from the road with a barrier if trees offers a total seclusion. 3 spacious bedrooms with walk-in-closets, 2 full updated baths, formal living room, formal dining room, den with wood burning fireplace for those cool nights. E.I.K., gleaming hardwood floors, updated heating system, Anderson windows, updated Architectural roof, 1 car garage, entertainment sized secluded yard that is fully fenced, deck, large basement adds endless potential for additional living space, room for pool. Conveniently located from Peconic Bay beaches, ocean beaches, Sag Harbor, Southampton Business District, parks, Shelter Island Ferry, golf and restaurants.
